headline: Pharma Stocks Are Close to Breaking Out. Earnings Could Set Them Free.
summary: Pharmaceutical stocks just broke out to new highs—and earnings could push them even higher.  The  exchange-traded fund is up 32% in the past six months to almost $57.  Also helping the rally is that healthcare companies are investing in artificial intelligence to help them identify revenue opportunities with lower costs, potentially lifting profit margins.

headline: Gilead price target raised to $145 from $140 at Truist
summary: Truist raised the firm’s price target on Gilead (GILD) to $145 from $140 and keeps a Buy rating on the shares as part of a broader research note previewing Q4 earnings in Biotech. The firm is adjusting Yeztugo numbers heading into Q4 EPS, tweaking its timelines based on updated guidance for near-term launches, including BIC/LEN in 2H25, US launch of Hepcludex, and expansion opportunity for Livdelzi, and also fine-tuning its estimates for the anito-cel launch following FDA guidance, the analyst t
